                           <desc>
                              <locus target="#58v" facs="059">Fol. 58v</locus> A small, red and black cross mark the midpoint of the Psalter</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <desc>Overlooked words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#2r #59v #74r #81r #82v #90v #129r #132v" facs="002 060 074 081 083 091 129 133">folss. 2r, 59v, 74r, 81r, 82v, 90v, 129r, 132v, </locus>);
                        and overlooked lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#14v #22r #23r #57v #78r #106r #129v" facs="015 022 023 058 078 106 130">14v, 22r, 23r, 57v, 78r, 106r, 129v</locus>)</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <desc>The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an appropriate aspect
                          ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe completes the line of text above the
                          end of the line (throughout). This scribe will also reduce the font size at the end of lines to avoid having to go onto the next line (throughout)</desc>
                        </item>

                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc>The general condition of the parchment is moderately dirty and relatively unworn. The parchment is fairly consistent and relatively thick</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc>
                              <locus target="#1r #140v" facs="001 141">Fols. 1r, 140v</locus> blank</desc>
                        </item>
                    </list>
